 {"id":"ft-5v7l0","title":"[golden] wa.search conformance golden freezes float fusion weights","description":"crates/frankenterm-core/tests/golden_robot_envelope/wa_search.json currently freezes raw float bytes for metrics.lexical_weight=0.30000001192092896 and metrics.semantic_weight=0.699999988079071. Those values originate from effective_search_fusion_weights in crates/frankenterm-core/src/mcp.rs:150-157 via f32 casting of quality_weight.\n\nRisk: these golden bytes are tied to representation details of the current float path rather than operator-visible wa.search behavior. A harmless implementation change (for example widening/narrowing intermediates, different serde float rendering, or moving the helper) can cause golden churn with no semantic regression. This is the same class of byte-stability issue as ft-55l4f: scheduler/config representation detail frozen as contract noise.\n\nFix direction: keep a semantic assertion on the search weights in the test harness, but canonicalize or round the serialized golden value so the golden freezes presence/meaning rather than exact float formatting artifacts.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-23T19:11:54.151063Z","created_by":"jemanuel","updated_at":"2026-04-23T19:25:21.461737Z","closed_at":"2026-04-23T19:25:21.461447Z","close_reason":"Fixed in 691661d2 (Option a: round to 2 decimals, matching pane 5 style precedent). canonicalize() in mcp_conformance_core_tools.rs now matches 'lexical_weight' | 'semantic_weight' if the child is a number, computes (f*100.0).round()/100.0, and stores it via serde_json::Number::from_f64 → Value::Number. The golden value is exactly 0.3 / 0.7 after round-trip because ryu emits shortest round-trip form for f64 0.3 / 0.7. wa_search.json golden pinned to the canonical 0.3 / 0.7 values. Kept the 30/70 split readable in the golden (reviewer can still see intent at a glance) instead of zeroing like score/semantic_score. Semantic assertions in assert_search_su